  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">ACT alliance Emergency work inside Syria SYR131 IOCC</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The Syrian conflict has resulted in a desperate humanitarian crisis in the region. Within Syria there are now more than 6 million people in need of humanitarian aid. IOCC is playing a significant role in providing this support. This food parcel distribution will help to provide nutrition to families who are facing desperate poverty due to the conflict.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">This project record reflects our contribution to the ACT Appeal SYR121 and is earmarked for IOCC&apos;s work inside Syria (GBP 100 000 Code 2)
IOCC&apos;s work within Syria covers:
Food for 24,000 pax; NFI for 6,800 pax. Psychosocial support for 150 pax. Subsidied school fees for 450 children. Rent support or shelter material for 2,400 pax. cash for work for 1,920 pax.

This funding will primarily cover a food parcel distribution over three months</narrative>
  </description>
